		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Ronin</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Miyamoto_Musashi_Painting.jpg" class="image" title="A painting by the famed ukiyo-e master Utagawa Kuniyoshi depicting famous ronin Miyamoto Musashi having his fortune told."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Miyamoto_Musashi_Painting.jpg/180px-Miyamoto_Musashi_Painting.jpg" width="180" height="269" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Miyamoto_Musashi_Painting.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
A painting by the famed <a href="/wiki/Ukiyo-e" title="Ukiyo-e">ukiyo-e</a> master <a href="/wiki/Utagawa_Kuniyoshi" title="Utagawa Kuniyoshi">Utagawa Kuniyoshi</a> depicting famous ronin <a href="/wiki/Miyamoto_Musashi" title="Miyamoto Musashi">Miyamoto Musashi</a> having his fortune told.</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="dablink">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Ronin_(disambiguation)" title="Ronin (disambiguation)">Ronin (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<p>A <b>ronin</b> <span style="font-weight: normal">(<span class="t_nihongo_kanji"><span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja">浪人</span></span> <span class="t_nihongo_comma" style="display:none">,</span><i><span class="t_nihongo_romaji">rōnin</span></i><span class="t_nihongo_help noprint"><sup><a href="/wiki/Help:Japanese" title="Help:Japanese"><span class="t_nihongo_icon" style="color: #00e; font: bold 80% sans-serif; text-decoration: none; padding: 0 .1em;">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> was a <a href="/wiki/Samurai" title="Samurai">samurai</a> with no lord or master during the <a href="/wiki/History_of_Japan#Feudal_Japan_.2812th_-_19th_century.29" title="History of Japan">feudal period (1185–1868)</a> of <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japan</a>. A samurai became masterless from the ruin or fall of his master, or after the loss of his master's favor or <a href="/wiki/Privilege" title="Privilege">privilege</a>.</p>
